verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, Concerning the feasts of the Lord, which ye shall proclaim to be holy convocations, even these are my feasts.
verses.verse_html: 2Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, Concerning the feasts of the Lord, which ye shall proclaim to be holy convocations, even these are my feasts.

verses.text_plain: Six days shall work be done: but the seventh day is the sabbath of rest, an holy convocation; ye shall do no work therein: it is the sabbath of the Lord in all your dwellings.
verses.verse_html: 3Six days shall work be done: but the seventh day is the sabbath of rest, an holy convocation; ye shall do no work therein: it is the sabbath of the Lord in all your dwellings.

verses.text_plain: These are the feasts of the Lord, even holy convocations, which ye shall proclaim in their seasons.
verses.verse_html: 4These are the feasts of the Lord, even holy convocations, which ye shall proclaim in their seasons.

verses.text_plain: In the fourteenth day of the first month at even is the Lord’s passover.
verses.verse_html: 5In the fourteenth day of the first month at even is the Lord’s passover.

verses.text_plain: And on the fifteenth day of the same month is the feast of unleavened bread unto the Lord: seven days ye must eat unleavened bread.
verses.verse_html: 6And on the fifteenth day of the same month is the feast of unleavened bread unto the Lord: seven days ye must eat unleavened bread.

verses.text_plain: In the first day ye shall have an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.
verses.verse_html: 7In the first day ye shall have an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.

verses.text_plain: But ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord seven days: in the seventh day is an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.
verses.verse_html: 8But ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord seven days: in the seventh day is an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 9And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come into the land which I give unto you, and shall reap the harvest thereof, then ye shall bring a sheaf of the firstfruits of your harvest unto the priest:
verses.verse_html:
10Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye be come into the land which I give unto you, and shall reap the harvest thereof, then ye shall bring a sheaf of the firstfruits of your harvest unto the priest: ▼
▼ sheaf: or, handful: Heb. omer

tokens.text: unto them, When ye be come

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sheaf: or, handful: Heb. omer

verses.text_plain: And he shall wave the sheaf before the Lord, to be accepted for you: on the morrow after the sabbath the priest shall wave it.
verses.verse_html: 11And he shall wave the sheaf before the Lord, to be accepted for you: on the morrow after the sabbath the priest shall wave it.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall offer that day when ye wave the sheaf an he lamb without blemish of the first year for a burnt offering unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 12And ye shall offer that day when ye wave the sheaf an he lamb without blemish of the first year for a burnt offering unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the meat offering thereof shall be two tenth deals of fine flour mingled with oil, an offering made by fire unto the Lord for a sweet savour: and the drink offering thereof shall be of wine, the fourth part of an hin.
verses.verse_html: 13And the meat offering thereof shall be two tenth deals of fine flour mingled with oil, an offering made by fire unto the Lord for a sweet savour: and the drink offering thereof shall be of wine, the fourth part of an hin.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall eat neither bread, nor parched corn, nor green ears, until the selfsame day that ye have brought an offering unto your God: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.
verses.verse_html: 14And ye shall eat neither bread, nor parched corn, nor green ears, until the selfsame day that ye have brought an offering unto your God: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall count unto you from the morrow after the sabbath, from the day that ye brought the sheaf of the wave offering; seven sabbaths shall be complete:
verses.verse_html: 15And ye shall count unto you from the morrow after the sabbath, from the day that ye brought the sheaf of the wave offering; seven sabbaths shall be complete:

verses.text_plain: Even unto the morrow after the seventh sabbath shall ye number fifty days; and ye shall offer a new meat offering unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16Even unto the morrow after the seventh sabbath shall ye number fifty days; and ye shall offer a new meat offering unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall bring out of your habitations two wave loaves of two tenth deals: they shall be of fine flour; they shall be baken with leaven; they are the firstfruits unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 17Ye shall bring out of your habitations two wave loaves of two tenth deals: they shall be of fine flour; they shall be baken with leaven; they are the firstfruits unto the Lord.

tokens.text: they shall be of fine flour

verses.text_plain: And ye shall offer with the bread seven lambs without blemish of the first year, and one young bullock, and two rams: they shall be for a burnt offering unto the Lord, with their meat offering, and their drink offerings, even an offering made by fire, of sweet savour unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 18And ye shall offer with the bread seven lambs without blemish of the first year, and one young bullock, and two rams: they shall be for a burnt offering unto the Lord, with their meat offering, and their drink offerings, even an offering made by fire, of sweet savour unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Then ye shall sacrifice one kid of the goats for a sin offering, and two lambs of the first year for a sacrifice of peace offerings.
verses.verse_html: 19Then ye shall sacrifice one kid of the goats for a sin offering, and two lambs of the first year for a sacrifice of peace offerings.

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall wave them with the bread of the firstfruits for a wave offering before the Lord, with the two lambs: they shall be holy to the Lord for the priest.
verses.verse_html: 20And the priest shall wave them with the bread of the firstfruits for a wave offering before the Lord, with the two lambs: they shall be holy to the Lord for the priest.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall proclaim on the selfsame day, that it may be an holy convocation unto you: ye shall do no servile work therein: it shall be a statute for ever in all your dwellings throughout your generations.
verses.verse_html: 21And ye shall proclaim on the selfsame day, that it may be an holy convocation unto you: ye shall do no servile work therein: it shall be a statute for ever in all your dwellings throughout your generations.

verses.text_plain: And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not make clean riddance of the corners of thy field when thou reapest, neither shalt thou gather any gleaning of thy harvest: thou shalt leave them unto the poor, and to the stranger: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 22And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not make clean riddance of the corners of thy field when thou reapest, neither shalt thou gather any gleaning of thy harvest: thou shalt leave them unto the poor, and to the stranger: I am the Lord your God.

tokens.text: thou shalt not make clean riddance

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 23And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, In the seventh month, in the first day of the month, shall ye have a sabbath, a memorial of blowing of trumpets, an holy convocation.
verses.verse_html: 24Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, In the seventh month, in the first day of the month, shall ye have a sabbath, a memorial of blowing of trumpets, an holy convocation.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall do no servile work therein: but ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 25Ye shall do no servile work therein: but ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 26And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Also on the tenth day of this seventh month there shall be a day of atonement: it shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall afflict your souls, and offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 27Also on the tenth day of this seventh month there shall be a day of atonement: it shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall afflict your souls, and offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord.

tokens.text: unto you; and ye shall afflict

verses.text_plain: And ye shall do no work in that same day: for it is a day of atonement, to make an atonement for you before the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 28And ye shall do no work in that same day: for it is a day of atonement, to make an atonement for you before the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: For whatsoever soul it be that shall not be afflicted in that same day, he shall be cut off from among his people.
verses.verse_html: 29For whatsoever soul it be that shall not be afflicted in that same day, he shall be cut off from among his people.

verses.text_plain: And whatsoever soul it be that doeth any work in that same day, the same soul will I destroy from among his people.
verses.verse_html: 30And whatsoever soul it be that doeth any work in that same day, the same soul will I destroy from among his people.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall do no manner of work: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.
verses.verse_html: 31Ye shall do no manner of work: it shall be a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.

verses.text_plain: It shall be unto you a sabbath of rest, and ye shall afflict your souls: in the ninth day of the month at even, from even unto even, shall ye celebrate your sabbath.
verses.verse_html:
32It shall be unto you a sabbath of rest, and ye shall afflict your souls: in the ninth day of the month at even, from even unto even, shall ye celebrate your sabbath. ▼
▼ celebrate: Heb. rest

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 33And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, The fifteenth day of this seventh month shall be the feast of tabernacles for seven days unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 34Speak unto the children of Israel, saying, The fifteenth day of this seventh month shall be the feast of tabernacles for seven days unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: On the first day shall be an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.
verses.verse_html: 35On the first day shall be an holy convocation: ye shall do no servile work therein.

verses.text_plain: Seven days ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord: on the eighth day shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord: it is a solemn assembly; and ye shall do no servile work therein.
verses.verse_html:
36Seven days ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord: on the eighth day shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord: it is a solemn assembly; and ye shall do no servile work therein. ▼
▼ solemn…: Heb. day of restraint

tokens.text: unto you; and ye shall offer

footnotes.body_html: ▼ solemn…: Heb. day of restraint

verses.text_plain: These are the feasts of the Lord, which ye shall proclaim to be holy convocations, to offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord, a burnt offering, and a meat offering, a sacrifice, and drink offerings, every thing upon his day:
verses.verse_html: 37These are the feasts of the Lord, which ye shall proclaim to be holy convocations, to offer an offering made by fire unto the Lord, a burnt offering, and a meat offering, a sacrifice, and drink offerings, every thing upon his day:

verses.text_plain: Beside the sabbaths of the Lord, and beside your gifts, and beside all your vows, and beside all your freewill offerings, which ye give unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 38Beside the sabbaths of the Lord, and beside your gifts, and beside all your vows, and beside all your freewill offerings, which ye give unto the Lord.

tokens.text: and beside all your freewill offerings

verses.text_plain: Also in the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when ye have gathered in the fruit of the land, ye shall keep a feast unto the Lord seven days: on the first day shall be a sabbath, and on the eighth day shall be a sabbath.
verses.verse_html: 39Also in the fifteenth day of the seventh month, when ye have gathered in the fruit of the land, ye shall keep a feast unto the Lord seven days: on the first day shall be a sabbath, and on the eighth day shall be a sabbath.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall take you on the first day the boughs of goodly trees, branches of palm trees, and the boughs of thick trees, and willows of the brook; and ye shall rejoice before the Lord your God seven days.
verses.verse_html:
40And ye shall take you on the first day the boughs of goodly trees, branches of palm trees, and the boughs of thick trees, and willows of the brook; and ye shall rejoice before the Lord your God seven days. ▼
▼ boughs of goodly trees: Heb. fruit of, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ boughs of goodly trees: Heb. fruit of, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ boughs of goodly trees: Heb. fruit of, etc

verses.text_plain: And ye shall keep it a feast unto the Lord seven days in the year. It shall be a statute for ever in your generations: ye shall celebrate it in the seventh month.
verses.verse_html: 41And ye shall keep it a feast unto the Lord seven days in the year. It shall be a statute for ever in your generations: ye shall celebrate it in the seventh month.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall dwell in booths seven days; all that are Israelites born shall dwell in booths:
verses.verse_html: 42Ye shall dwell in booths seven days; all that are Israelites born shall dwell in booths:

verses.text_plain: That your generations may know that I made the children of Israel to dwell in booths, when I brought them out of the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 43That your generations may know that I made the children of Israel to dwell in booths, when I brought them out of the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: And Moses declared unto the children of Israel the feasts of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 44And Moses declared unto the children of Israel the feasts of the Lord.
